Hi,

while I generally love the vi mode (which more software should have), =20=

there is a minor quirk: when I recall a previous command line (by =20
pressing the up arrow), the cursor is at the beginning rather than the =20=

end of the command line. As I mostly want to change commands from the =20=

end this means 3 extra keystrokes every time just to get there.

Is there a way I can change this, so that in vi mode the cursor is =20
initially at the end of the recalled command line (as it is in emacs =20
mode)?

